iately after the mortality salience manipulation, ask participants to judge the moral acceptability of the target action in the harm-conflict and harm control versions of our two scenarios (that is, they read a total of four scenarios). \n6. Compute the rate of utilitarian responses across scenarios and conduct an ANOVA with mortality salience (death vs. pain) as a between-subjects factor and scenario version (harm-conflict vs. harm-control) as a within-subjects factor.",
